ation, visions of nationhood, the likeness of Jesus, the material life of words, and the role of modern art as a spiritual quest, to the importance of images for education, devotion, worship, and domestic life. An insightful, informed presentation of how Christianity has shaped and continues to shape the modern world, this work is a must-read for scholars and students across fields of religious studies, history, and art history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aChristianity and artxCatholic ChurchxHistory. 0aChristianity and artxProtestant churchesxHistory 0aChristianity and artxProtestant churchesxHistory. 0aChristianityxPhilosophy. 0aChurch historyyModern period, 1500- 0aChurch historyyModern period, 1500-. 0aImaginationxReligious aspectsxHistory. 0aProtestant churchesxRelationsxCatholic Church. 0aWord (Theology) 0aWord (Theology). 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  aart historians.  aart history.  aart.  aartists.  acatholic art.  acatholicism.  achristian art.  achristianity.  achristians.  achurch history.  achurch.  adivine art.  aearly modern religion.  afaith.  ahistory of christianity.  ahistory.  aholy art.  aholy images.  aholy vision.  aimage of christ.  alikeness of jesus.  amodern art.  amodern christianity.  aprotestantism.  areligion.  areligious art.  areligious education.  areligious imagination.  areligious studies.  asacred art.  asacred images.  avisible word.  avisual culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028695540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096199940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961999423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520961999/original 